Text.string: Hay, Vault Hunter. This cultist sumbitch who calls himself the Holy Dumptruck—well, he's been talking crap about the Raiders. That won't stand, amigo. Go tear him a new hole or two or seven! I ain't as concerned with the precise number as the outcome, you understand.
That said, might be right to just go ahead and shoot him in the ass! That'll send a lesson to the other bandits not to mess with the Raiders.
VH, don't forget to look all over the place for what ya need. Up, down, all around. But in this case: up.
Look, I'll just spell it out for ya: if you shoot that water pipe up there, it'll make a puddle. Then hit the switch on that generator. That should open the door.

Hoh-damn! Look at that! That's called a “red chest” in bandit speak—prob'ly 'cause of blood or somethin'. Bandits are happier about blood than a tick on a skag's ass. Anyways, you're always more likely to find good stuff in them red chests. They're usually hidden pretty good, though. So you'll have to really search 'em out. But it's worth it! Thanks for takin' care of that Dumptruck situation, sweet thang.
Oh, and this is for addin' insult to injury, shootin' Dumptruck in the ol' derriere like that.
You can jes kill him—but if you're feelin' it, shoot that bastard right in his backside!
Dumptruck's in the neighborhood. I can practically smell the sumbitch. Look around, VH.
Nice killin', VH! Pretty sure that dumbass Dumptruck was sitting on a loot stash. See if you can find it.
Dumptruck's stash is prob'ly behind a secret trap door. Might need to do somethin' special to get it open.
If you find somethin' to complete that electrical connection on the ground, that might do the trick.
